Kibo — Third-Party Notices
==========================

This file records the third-party components used by Kibo's Live2D rendering
pipeline, their versions as pinned in this repository, and their licenses.
See `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-live2d-renderer-design.md` §3 and §13
for the product/licensing decisions this list supports.

This file does not itself constitute legal advice or a completed license
audit for public distribution — see the "Live2D Cubism Core" section below
for the hard gate that still applies before any public release build may
ship.


1. PixiJS
---------
Version:  8.19.0 (pinned exactly in package.json, no `^` float — see design
          doc §13)
License:  MIT
Source:   https://github.com/pixijs/pixijs
Used for: WebGL rendering engine underlying the Live2D pet renderer
          (`Live2DPetRenderer` in `src/renderer/live2dRenderer.ts`).


2. untitled-pixi-live2d-engine
------------------------------
Version:  1.3.5 (pinned exactly in package.json — see design doc §13, and
          the Phase 4 pre-spike findings in design doc §17.2 for the
          version-compatibility caveats with Cubism Core below)
License:  MIT
Source:   https://www.npmjs.com/package/untitled-pixi-live2d-engine
Used for: The community PixiJS↔Cubism integration layer that loads and
          drives `*.model3.json` Live2D models inside a Pixi `Application`
          (imported via its `./cubism` subpath only, not the default export
          — see design doc §17.2 for why: the default export unconditionally
          pulls in legacy Cubism 2 runtime code this project does not use).
Note:     Design doc §17.2 records one version-compatibility bug found
          during the Phase 4 pre-spike: this engine version's compiled
          output assumes Cubism Core exposes a public
          `drawables.renderOrders` field, but the specific Cubism Core
          build in this repo (see below) makes that field private,
          reachable only via `getRenderOrders()`. A runtime compatibility
          patch for this is implemented in
          `src/renderer/live2dCubismCoreCompat.ts`.


