**Public-distribution gate (design doc §3):** per Live2D's SDK license,
shipping this file inside a publicly-distributed application (the
"Expandable Application" scenario Kibo's product design falls under)
requires Live2D's written approval and a signed publisher agreement before
a public release build may include it. This is Phase 8 of the Live2D
rendering roadmap (design doc §16) and has not happened yet — do not build
or distribute a public installer that bundles this file until Phase 8 is
complete. Development, internal proof-of-concept, and local testing (this
repository's current state) are explicitly permitted without that approval
per Live2D's SDK license terms — see design doc §3 for the full reasoning
and official reference links.


4. Scope note
-------------
This list covers the Live2D rendering stack specifically (the subject of
`docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-live2d-renderer-design.md`). Kibo has
other third-party runtime dependencies (Electron, its voice TTS backends,
etc.) tracked via `package.json` / `pnpm-lock.yaml` and their own
upstream licenses (all permissive — MIT/Apache/BSD-family — as of this
writing); this file does not attempt to enumerate the full dependency
tree, only the components specific to the Live2D licensing decision this
design doc addresses.
